basic.Peptide Name: Caeridin-a1 (Gly-rich; Leu-rich; natural AMPs; frog, amphibians, animals; XXA)
basic.Source: Skin Secretion, Australian White's Tree Frog,Litoria caerulea, Australia
basic.Target Organism: Active against S. aureus NCTC10788 (MIC 8 uM), MRSA NCTC12493 (MIC 16 uM), E. faecalis NCTC12697 (MIC 32 uM), E. coli NCTC10418 (MIC 32 uM), and C. albicans NCYC1467 (MIC 32 uM). Helical in 50% TFE.
